Phn I. L thuyt
1. Although/ Even though/ Though
- Ba lin t ny thng u cu hoc gia hai mnh . Nu ng u
cu th gia 2 mnh phi c du phy
- Although/ though/ even though u c cng ngha nhng though khi ng
u cu gip cu ni tr nn trang trng hn so vi khi n ng gia hai
mnh cn even though mang ngha nhn mnh hn
- i khi trong vn ni, chng ta thng dng though cui cu.
SCu trc: Although/ though/ even though + S + V.., S + V
Eg: Although I dont agree with him, I think hes honest. (Mc d ti khng
ng vi anh ta nhng ti ngh anh ta rt thnh tht.)
2. In spite of/ Despite
Cu trc: In spite of/ Despite + Noun/ Noun phrase/ Gerund phrase
Eg: Despite being ill, Mary still went to school. (D b m nhng Mary vn i
hc.)
- Despite v in spite of ng trc mt danh t
- Despite v in spite of ng trc i t (this/ that/ what)
- Despite v in spite of ng trc V-ing
- Chng ta c th s dng in spite of v despite vi cm t the fact that
- C despite v in spite of c th c dng mnh u hoc mnh
th hai u c
3. Cc cng thc bin i cu vi Although sang cu vi Despite
*Nu ch ng ca 2 mnh ging nhau th ta b ch ng ri ly ng t
thm ing:
Although + S + V In spite of/ Despite + V_ing
V d: Although he was ill, he still went to school.
Despite being ill, he still went to school.
*Nu ch ng l danh t + be + tnh t th ta em tnh t t trc danh t,
b to be:
Although + The + N + Be + Adj In spite of/Despite + The + Adj + N
V d: Although the car was dirty, he didnt wash it.
Despite / in spite of the dirty car, he didnt wash it.
*Nu ch ng l i t + be + tnh t th ta i i t thnh s hu, i tnh
t thnh danh t, b be
Although + S + Be + Adj In spite of/ Despite + His /her/ their + N
V d: Although he was ill, he still went to school.
Despite his illness, he still went to school.
*Thm the fact that trc mnh :
Although + S + V In spite of/ Despite + The fact that + S + V
V d: Although I studied very hard, I failed the placement test.
Despite the fact that I studied very hard, I failed the placement test.
Phn II. Bi tp
Task 1. Choose the best answer to complete these sentences.
1. ___B____ he likes chocolate, he tries not to eat it.
A. as
B.though
C. since
D. despite
2. ________D_______ he had enough money, he refused to buy a new car.
A. In spite
B. In spite of
C. Despite
D. Although
3. _______A________, he walked to the station.
A. Despite being tired
B. Although to be tired
C. In spite being tired
D. Despite tired
4. ________C________ her lack of hard work, she was promoted.
A. Because
B. Even though
C. In spite of
D. Despite of
5. She left him _______B________ she still loved him.
A. even if
B. even though
C. in spite of
D. despite
Task 2. Choose the best answer to complete these sentences.
1. Mr. Ba was late for the meeting though he took a taxi.
A. Even though taking a taxi, Mr. Ba was late for the meeting.
B. In spite of taking a taxi, but Mr. Ba was late for the meeting.
C. Mr. Ba was late for the meeting despite the fact he took a taxi.
D. Mr. Ba was late for the meeting although having taken a taxi.
2. We came to the meeting on time though the traffic was heavy.
A. Despite the traffic was heavy; we came to the meeting on time.
B. In spite of the heavy traffic, we came to the meeting on time.
C. Even though the heavy traffic, we came to the meeting on time.
D. Although the traffic was heavy, but we came to the meeting on time.
3. Although he took a taxi, Bill still arrived late for the concert.
A. Bill arrived late for the concert whether he took a taxi or not.
B. Bill arrived late for the concert because of the taxi.
C. In spite of taking a taxi, Bill arrived late for the concert.
D. Bill took a taxi to the concert, but he couldnt catch it.
4. Although she is rich, she cant afford to buy the car.
A. She doesnt have enough money to buy the car she likes.
B. Rich as she is, she cant afford to buy the car.
C. The car is too expensive for her to buy.
D. She wants to buy the car but it costs a lot.
5. Although Sue felt tired, she stayed up late talking to Jill.
A. Despite feeling tired, Sue stayed up late talking to Jill.
B. In spite feeling tired, Sue stayed up late talking to Jill.
C. Sue wouldnt feel tired despite staying up late talking to Jill.
D. Sue stayed up late talking to Jill. As a result, she was tired.

Task 4. Vit li cu.
1. Although Nam is not an intelligent student, he can learn very fast.
Despite / In spite of not being an intelligent student, he can learn very
fast
2. Because Hoa was rich, she could buy that house.
Because of being rich, Hoa could buy that house
3. Because the rain was so heavy, I couldn't go to school.
Because of the heavy rain, I couldnt go to school
4. His father asked him to go stay at home because he was sick.
Because of being sick, his father asked him to go stay at home
5. Because there was an accident, I was late.
Because of the accident, I was late

the heating was on

Task 6. Make one sentence from two. Use the word(s) in brackets in
your sentences.
1. I couldn't sleep. I was very tired.
(despite) I couldn't sleep despite being vey tired.
2. They have very little money. They are happy.
(in spite of) in spite of having very little money, they are happy
3. My foot was injured. I managed to walk to the nearest village.
(although) Although my food wuas injured, I managed to walk to the
nearest village
4. I enjoyed the film. The story was silly.
(in spite of) in spite of enjoying the film, the story was silly
5. We live in the same street. We hardly ever see each other.
(despite) despite living in the same street, we hardly ever see each other
6. I got very wet in the rain. I was only out for five minutes.
(even though) even though I got very wet in the rain, I was only out for
five minutes

Sometimes, two answers are possible.
